750322,0.03212837,0.01591328,0.04123414,-0.01764824,-0.01086562,-0.00587541,0.05244485,-0.04463150,-0.02247319,0.07191446,-0.01807940,-0.01289661,0.02976547,-0.04074316,0.02525192,-0.00769435,0.03981951,-0.05853314,0.07834850,-0.09057211,0.04196441,0.10588949,-0.01340511,0.00495594,-0.03897384,0.01566198,0.00970876,0.06780943,-0.02838933,0.01001851,0.04628569,0.03250950,0.07253227,0.01723729,0.02680339,-0.03252705,0.02955330,0.05749834,0.04827395,0.06454851,0.04830022,-0.03091925]',E'MySQL Server Version Compatibility\n\nAll MySQL users are strongly encouraged to always upgrade to the latest version of MySQL Shell, regardless of the MySQL Server version they''re using.\n\nThe latest version of MySQL Shell is fully backwards compatible with all supported versions of MySQL Server (**9.x** and **8.4**).\n\nMySQL Shell also supports older versions of MySQL (**8.0** and older) for a variety of specific purposes in a best-effort basis:\n\n* Basic SQL query functionality (MySQL 5.7 and 8.0)\n* Upgrade Checker (MySQL 5.7 and 8.0)\n* Dump and load utilities (MySQL 5.6, 5.7 and 8.0)\n  * Note: downgrades (loading dumps into older MySQL servers than the original) are not supported, although they might work in some cases.\n* AdminAPI (MySQL 8.0)','{"source": "mysql", "version": "9.0", "language": "sql", "title": "MySQL Shell", "section_title": "README", "url": "https://github.com/mysql/mysql-shell/blob/master/README.md", "topics": "mysql/shell,README", "categories": "database,sql,relational,shell,cli"}');
